cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.DS

The paper deals with the generalization error of learning algorithms, which is a central topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses information theory to analyze the generalization capability, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely category. The paper proposes algorithms for controlling the input-output mutual information, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with the theoretical analysis of learning algorithms, which could also fit under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
